FIELD DESCRIPTION: source containing additional documentation on parameters ; USHIS - Stover, C.W. and Coffman, J. L., 1993, Seismicity of the United States, 1568 Ð 1989, U.S. Geological Survey Professional Paper 1527, 418 pp
year of earthquake occurrence
month of earthquake occurrence
day of earthquake occurrence
hour of earthquake occurrence; left blank if time is not known
minute of earthquake occurrence; if hour is known, but minute is unknown, minute is represented as 0
second of earthquake occurrence, if hour is known, but second is unknown, second is represented as 0
"Z" -  epicenter determined from macroseismic data;  blank - epicenter constrained or determined by seismographic data
geographic latitude, south negative
geographic longitude, west negative
focal-depth in km
short-period body wave magnitude, usually that listed in the PDE bulletin of the USGS/National Earthquake Information Center and predecessor agencies
long-period (~ 20s) surface-wave magnitude,  usually that listed in the PDE bulletin of the USGS/National Earthquake Information Center and predecessor agencies
first-listed magnitude that is not mb(PDE) or Ms(PDE)

type of magnitude 1; "FA" - based on felt area; "Lg" - based on short-period Lg phase; "mb" - body-wave magnitude; "MD" - duration magnitude; "ML" - local magnitude; "MS" - surface-wave magnitude; "Mw" - moment magnitude; "UK" - magnitude-type unknown;  more documentation in Stover and Coffman (1993)
source of magnitude 1, documented in Stover and Coffman (1993)
second-listed magnitude that is not mb(PDE) or Ms(PDE)

type of magnitude 2; "FA" - based on felt area; "Lg" - based on short-period Lg phase; "mb" - body-wave magnitude; "MD" - duration magnitude; "ML" - local magnitude; "MS" - surface-wave magnitude; "UK" - magnitude-type unknown;  more documentation in Stover and Coffman (1989)
source of magnitude 2, documented in Stover and Coffman (1993)
Flinn-Engdahl region
qualitative estimate of precision, from "A" = highest precision to "I" = lowest precision;

maximum observed Modified Mercalli Intensity (MMI) on a scale of 1-12; for non-U.S. shocks for which the MMI near the epicenter is not known, the maximum intensity in the U.S. is given; '.' signifies that data were insufficient to estimate an MMO

"F" -- earthquake was reported felt; "." -- documentation of the earthquake being felt was not available to Stover and Coffman(1993); sometimes observations establish that earthquake was felt, but are insufficient to estimate a Modified Mercalli Intensity (MMI)
parameter listed in USHIS whose significance is not known to us
